"""Splice Circus

std::list and std::forward_list do things no array-backed container can: move a chunk of nodes between lists without copying a single element, keep an iterator alive across that move, and hand you a member sort() because there is no random access for std::sort to use. Predict the exact output of seven programs that put those tricks through their paces.
"""
